      "name": "CFD model correctly identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under CPB conditions",
      "description": "The CFD hemolysis model, applied across all five flow-speed operating points, correctly rank-orders pump configurations by hemolytic potential and identifies the worst-case condition within the tolerance envelope. The relative hemolysis index (RH) computed by the model satisfies RH < 1 relative to the predicate device across all evaluated configurations, supporting regulatory acceptance of the tolerance design. This claim is substantiated by the credibility factor assessments documented in this package and by the validation activities summarized in the associated ValidationResult nodes.",
      "scope": "FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry, MRL 2, Class II CPB device, flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM",
      "purpose": "Regulatory submission support for 510(k) tolerance analysis of centrifugal blood pump impeller geometry"
    }
